Engineering Manager (PSS/201209/03/SG)
Job ID
EPM-00003250
Country
Singapore
State/Province
Singapore
City
Singapore
Publish Start Date
Sep 25 2012
Job Level
Supervisor / Manager
|
Responsibilities:
Responsible for leading a high-performance team of engineers, their training and personnel development.
Ensure compliance with Project Management Office standards and following industry standard practices and meeting client requirements.
Ensure team meets hours estimates & support productivity programs to improve efficiency.
Responsible for overall staffing of the group including achieving operational effectiveness goals.
Interface to Best Cost Engineering Centers for Singapore project needs, including effective use of deputation and off-shore assignments.
Drive overall performance of group through use of lessons learned sessions & sharing of best practices.
Support Singapore Sales (including mega-project pursuit team) in pursuits, estimating, presentations, demonstrations, and site surveys.
Drive lessons learned, sharing, toolkit development & knowledge management in general as well productivity improvements and understanding of rework and areas of improvement.
Direct the project implementation team and adhere closely to the contractual obligation during implementation phase.
Ensure complete project engineering documentation, system start up & successful commissioning at site & ISO engineering standards are implemented at all times and timely shipment of projects.
Requirements:
Diploma/Degree in Engineering with minimum 7 years working experience in process control systems or project management.
Leadership quality, ability to negotiate and work effectively in a team oriented group.
Good analytical, interpersonal and communication skills.